description: Uday Nagaraju, a computer engineer interested in AI, is Labour's candidate from North Bedfordshire in UK general elections. He aims to give voice to the community and challenges the Conservative bastion.
title: PIO from Hyderabad to fight UK polls as Labour candidate

description: Maharashtra deputy chief minister Ajit Pawar's close aide Chhagan Bhujbal faced delays in being announced as the candidate for Nashik. CM Eknath Shinde's push for a candidate of his choice reflects the political battle with pro-Uddhav Thackeray sentiment. OBC voter dynamics play a crucial role in the unfolding political scenario in Nashik.
title: As Sena faces Sena, Nashik battle hinges on loyalty-legitimacy

description: Bongaon, a critical Lok Sabha constituency on the India-Bangladesh border, witnesses a quiet period before polling. The Matua community, dominant with 70% of voters, is central. Concerns about CAA-NRC, lack of election activity, and key figures like Amit Shah and Mamata Banerjee shape the electoral landscape.
title: CAA doubts ring loud amid poll hush in Matua hub

description: Supreme Court rules writ petitions by erstwhile employees against Air India post privatization by Tata group in Jan 2022 are not maintainable as it ceased to be a public body under administrative control after disinvestment, no longer falling under the writ jurisdiction of the Constitution.
title: No writ petition can be filed against Air India, rules SC

description: Supreme Court's ruling enforces Article 300A, protecting landowners' rights. It specifies seven procedural rights and duties, including fair compensation and efficient acquisition conduct. The court also quashed Kolkata Municipal Corporation's illegal acquisition for a public park at Narkeldanga North Road.
title: Land acquisition valid only if it passes constitutional test: SC

description: Voter turnout in Lok Sabha polls is at 67%, with 45.1 crore of 97 crore electors voting. Polling data show a dip in turnout in first three phases compared to 2019, narrowing gap in fourth phase. EC emphasizes timely distribution of voter information slips.
title: Turnout in 1st 4 phases of LS polls at 67%; 45.1cr voted: EC

description: The Supreme Court rejected Arvind Kejriwal's plea challenging his arrest, emphasizing judicial restraint and fair decision-making by ED officers. The hearing involved arguments by Solicitor General Tushar Mehta and senior advocate Abhishek Manu Singhvi, addressing the misuse of liberty and the need for a balanced view in arrests.
title: No exception made for Kejriwal: SC on interim bail, arrest plea

description: IMD announced a near-normal monsoon onset over Kerala, indicating timely rains over parts of south peninsular India, Northeast, and Maharashtra. Top weather experts supported the favorable scenario for the monsoon progression. The absence of potential cyclone formations over the Arabian Sea or Bay of Bengal suggested a smooth monsoon flow.
title: Monsoon to arrive on time in Maha & Northeast: Experts

description: The Madhya Pradesh high court has declined to allow medical termination of pregnancy for a juvenile girl who was allegedly raped by her brother-in-law, after she and her mother testified in court that they would strive to save the accused during the trial. Nobody can be allowed to play hide and seek to commit murder of an unborn child, Justice G S Ahluwalia said in his April 22 order.
title: 'Can't allow misuse of court to kill unwanted child': HC rejects MTP plea

description: PM Modi defends media stance, criticizes past leaders for compromising Election Commission's independence. Points to historical instances of Constitution tampering by Nehru, Indira, Rajiv Gandhi, and Rahul Gandhi, highlighting media restrictions and court judgments overturned.
title: Don't do pressers as media not neutral, says PM Modi
'Looking at right time to list Flipkart'

description: Amit Shah pledges to ban cow slaughter and 'straighten' offenders, targeting Congress, Lalu Prasad, and PFI. Vows to build a grand temple at Punaura Dham, birthplace of Sita, in Bihar if NDA wins third term. Emphasizes BJP's commitment to development in Bihar.
title: In 3rd term, NDA will ban cow slaughter, build Sita temple: Amit Shah

description: Norges Bank excludes Adani Ports from its pension fund over ethical concerns following COE's recommendations. Adani Ports' ties with Myanmar's armed forces led to the exclusion. The sale of its Myanmar port to Solar Energy raises questions about its current connections.
title: 'War ties': Norway fund to sell Adani Ports stake

description: Supreme Court restricts ED's arrest power under PMLA post special court's cognisance. Justices A S Oka and Ujjal Bhuyan emphasize Section 4 of PMLA, Article 21 rights, and accused treatment post-summons. Writing the judgment, Justice Oka said once the special court takes cognisance, ED loses the power to arrest the accused, who in turn cannot apply for anticipatory bail.
title: ED can't arrest accused once court takes cognisance of complaint: SC

description: Rakhi Sawant has updated the media about her health, revealing that she has a 10 cm tumor in her uterus. She will be undergoing surgery to address the condition.
title: Rakhi Sawant confirms she has tumor; says 'surgery on Saturday'

description: Trinamool Congress lodged a complaint with the Election Commission against BJP's Tamluk candidate Abhijit Gangopadhyay for misogynistic remarks towards Mamata Banerjee at a campaign rally in Chaitanyapur, East Midnapore. State finance minister Chandrima Bhattacharya condemned Gangopadhyay's derogatory language. Mamata Banerjee, campaigning in Haldia, did not address the issue.
title: Ex-judge, BJP pick on Mamata: 'What is your price?'

description: Nearly one-third of Covaxin recipients experienced adverse events of special interest within a year, including respiratory, skin, and musculoskeletal issues. The study also highlighted menstrual abnormalities in 5% of women. AstraZeneca's vaccine technology controversy and Covishield's development by the Serum Institute of India are notable. The study reported viral upper respiratory tract infections in adolescents and adults.
title: 1 in 3 Covaxin recipients hit by adverse events: Study

description: According to the Mastercard Economics Institute's "travel trends 2024: breaking boundaries" research issued Thursday, the top five trending locations for Indian travelers this summer (June - August) are Amsterdam, Singapore, London, Frankfurt, and Melbourne.
title: 'Amsterdam among top travel spots for Indians'

description: In 2023, Schengen countries, including India, faced a 44% surge in visa applications, reaching 9.7 lakh. India ranked second in application increase after China, followed by Morocco. The war on Ukraine affected travel plans, and VFS Global faced criticism for visa appointment unavailability.
title: Schengen visa interview slots elusive this summer as demand shoots up

description: Ego Media's hoardings on railway land in Dadar East exceed BMC's size limits, prompting a notice from Ashwini Joshi. BMC's policy restricts hoarding sizes and specifies limits for different structures.
title: 7 hoardings of ad companies in breach of BMC cap on railway land

description: Bhavesh Bhinde, director of the company behind the Ghatkopar hoarding collapse, was arrested in Udaipur. Show-cause notice issued to IPS officer Quaiser Khalid. Bhinde fled to Lonavala and Thane after the incident.
title: Billboard co chief held from Raj; DGP notice to ex-Mum GRP head

description: Twelve persons, including Monojit Mondal, Samar Mridha, Chandan Sahani, Asit Saha, Atul Mandal, Sabidul Sk, Priyanka Singha, Nyan Roy, Sumitra Mandal, Suitara Biwi, Pankaj Mandal, and a Budhia woman, were killed and five wounded by lightning during a thunderstorm in Malda and Murshidabad, West Bengal. Disaster management personnel were deployed to rescue the wounded victims.
title: Lightning kills 12 in WB, many of them were picking mangoes

description: Mamata Banerjee clarifies Trinamool Congress's role in the INDIA bloc, stating they are a part of the coalition in Bengal. She emphasized that her party is the only INDIA bloc party in Bengal. Local CPM, Congress are not part of the coalition, seen as BJP agents. Congress seniors from Delhi did not attend meetings for their candidates.
title: A day after offering outside aid, Didi says will join INDIA govt

description: In Kota, a three-year-old girl suffocated to death in a locked car during a wedding. Pradeep Nagar mistakenly left Gorvika for over two hours at Jorawarpur village. The parents, engaged in separate groups, realized she was missing after two hours.
title: 3-year-old dies as parents forget her in car, go for wedding

description: On Thursday, Prime Minister Narendra Modi accused the Congress of using secularism as a smokescreen to practice communal politics until he exposed the party's divisive agenda, claiming that the ongoing Lok Sabha elections are a contest between "santushtikaran" (ensuring people's satisfaction) and "tushtikaran" (appeasement).
title: PM Modi calls LS polls contest of 'santushtikaran vs tushtikaran'

description: Maulana Imamuddin, 40, died in an explosion near a madrassa in Saran, Bihar. The blast, caused by a suspected bomb, injured Noor Alam, 15, who is receiving treatment at Patna Medical College Hospital.
title: Maulana dead, student hurt in blast outside Bihar madrassa

description: A 62-year-old man, Maniram Jatav, was killed and eaten by a tiger near Bhopal. Forest officials set up camera traps in Ratapani Wildlife Sanctuary. The victim, collecting tendu leaves, received compensation. Villagers are warned against forest visits after sunset. Two tigers were sighted in the area recently, with one near a university.
title: Tiger kills man in MP, feasts on his body

description: Schools in Lucknow, led by Anil Agarwal, offer innovative rewards for students whose parents vote on May 21, including 10 extra marks and an extra day's salary for staff to boost voting percentage in Lucknow Lok Sabha polls.
title: To boost voting, UP schools announce extra marks, pay

description: In Kozhikode, Kerala, a 4-year-old girl from Cheruvannur underwent surgery on her tongue instead of for polydactyly, due to medical negligence by Dr. Bejohn Johnson without parental consent at IMCH. The police have registered a case under IPC sections 336 and 337 for investigation. Health Minister Veena George has ordered a detailed probe by DME.
title: Kid in hospital for finger surgery, operated on tongue instead

description: Arrested Alamgir Alam, the Jharkhand minister for rural development, allegedly received bribes from every contractor awarded work under his ministry, with payoffs totaling 1.5% of the value of the allocated work, according to the Enforcement Directorate's remand note filed on Wednesday. Alam was sentenced to six days in ED custody.
title: Alamgir took 1.5% cut from every contractor who got work: ED

description: The Indian Premier League (IPL) playoffs scenarios have taken an intriguing turn following the washout of the Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH) and Gujarat Titans (GT) match on Thursday. The unexpected outcome pushed SRH into the playoffs, while simultaneously eliminating the Delhi Capitals (DC) from contention. The spotlight now shifts to the Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Chennai Super Kings (CSK) clash on Saturday, which has morphed into a high-stakes knockout game.
title: IPL: Race for 2nd spot intensifies after SRH qualify for playoffs

description: A Supreme Court bench recalled a verdict for breaching 'stare decisis' judicial discipline and criticized a previous judgment on the Bhagat Ram case. The bench faulted the judgment for ignoring the 1967 Bhagat Ram case ruling on redistribution of unused land among original owners.
title: 2-judge bench recalls another 2-judge bench’s 3-yr-old order
‘Kejriwal has lost his mind after going to jail’: Yogi Adityanath

description: MS Dhoni's appearance on the cricket field is always a mesmerizing spectacle for fans, regardless of the match's outcome. In anticipation of the eagerly awaited and crucial clash between Chennai Super Kings and Royal Challengers Bangalore, a video emerged on CSK's social media platform, revealing MS Dhoni bowling during the team's practice session.
title: MS Dhoni bowls in nets ahead of CSK vs RCB clash

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad secured their spot in the Indian Premier League playoffs as rain prevented any play in their IPL match against Gujarat Titans. With this, SRH became the third team to qualify, following Kolkata Knight Riders and Rajasthan Royals, who currently hold the top two positions in the standings. Although the match was washed out, Sunrisers earned one point, bringing their tally to 15 points with one game remaining. Their final league fixture will be against Punjab Kings, who have already been eliminated, scheduled for May 19.
title: SRH in IPL playoff after rain washes out GT tie

description: Following his move to Saudi-backed Al-Nassr, world's most popular footballer Cristiano Ronaldo's estimated total earnings reached approximately $260 million, a record-breaking figure for a soccer player. His on-field earnings accounted for $200 million, with an additional $60 million derived from lucrative sponsorship deals, leveraging his massive Instagram following of 629 million.
title: Where does Ronaldo stand on Forbes' list?

description: In an astonishing turn of events, the Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) dressing room was graced by an unanticipated visitor on Thursday, none other than the legendary Chennai Super Kings (CSK) icon, MS Dhoni. RCB and CSK are set to engage in a pivotal encounter that will determine their play-off fate at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru on Saturday.
title: Watch: Dhoni's surprise visit in RCB dressing room

description: After giving statement to Delhi Police on in connection with the alleged assault by Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal's aide, Aam Aadmi Party MP Swati Maliwal said "the last few days have been very difficult" and she hopes "appropriate action will be taken" now after her statement. This is her first reaction after the alleged assault on her on Monday at CM Kejriwal's residence.
title: 'What happened to me was very bad': Maliwal breaks silence on assault, gives statement to cops

description: The Election Commission expressed discontent regarding the post-election turmoil in Andhra Pradesh and has issued clear instructions to the chief secretary and DGP to take measures to prevent any such incidents from happening again. All superintendents of police (SPs) have been directed to proactively implement preventive measures to deter similar occurrences in the future.
title: Post-poll violence: EC tells MHA to retain central forces in Andhra

description: Bhavesh Bhinde, owner of Ego Media Pvt Ltd, was arrested by the Mumbai police for a hoarding collapse in Ghatkopar that killed 16 people and injured 75 others. The incident occurred on May 13 during a dust storm and rain, when a 250-tonne, 120 x 120 sq ft hoarding fell onto a busy petrol pump, trapping nearly 100 people. The hoarding was erected without permission from the BMC.
title: Mumbai hoarding collapse: Owner Bhavesh Bhinde arrested

description: At least 11 people were killed and two others injured in lightning strikes in West Bengal's Malda district, police said. Two of the deceased were minors, both residents of Manikchak police station area, while three hailed from Sahapur under the jurisdiction of Malda police station, police added. A couple passed away in Harishchandrapur.
title: 11 killed in lightning in West Bengal's Malda

description: RCB have staged a remarkable turnaround in the tournament, climbing from the bottom of the table after losing seven of their first eight matches. Winning five consecutive games, they've ignited their campaign with impressive style. Meanwhile, defending champions CSK have encountered hurdles in their pursuit of a sixth IPL title, suffering three defeats in their last five matches.
title: Fan reveals plan to breach RCB vs CSK match security

description: Delhi Police recorded the statement of AAP Rajya Sabha MP Swati Maliwal on Thursday regarding the alleged assault on her by chief minister Arvind Kejriwal's aide Bibhav Kumar. The statement of Maliwal was recorded by a team of Delhi Police at her home in Central Delhi. Maliwal also informed the police about the incident that occurred at the chief minister's house.
title: Maliwal records statement in assault case, tells police about what happened at CM's house

description: Ahead of the highly anticipated match at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium, Suresh Raina, who was present at the stadium for his broadcasting duties, had a heartwarming reunion with his former India teammate, Virat Kohli. The two cricket stars, who have shared numerous memorable moments on the field, came together before the make-or-break RCB-CSK clash in Bengaluru.
title: 'Good to see you, brother!': Raina wishes Kohli best

description: A billboard collapsed in Pune's Pimpri Chinchwad area due to strong winds, similar to Mumbai's incident. No injuries were reported. On May 13, Ego Media Pvt Ltd hoarding in Mumbai caused 16 deaths and over 75 injured. BMC found illegal hoardings by Ego Media Pvt Ltd and issued a notice. Agencies provided the information.
title: Hoarding collapses in Pune days after 14 killed in Mumbai

description: CERT-In issued a 'high' severity warning for Google Chrome desktop version due to vulnerabilities allowing remote attackers to obtain sensitive information. Multiple high-severity security flaws found in select versions, including Type Confusion in V8, Use after free in Dawn, and Use after free in V8. Users advised to install security updates to address these issues.
title: Govt has a warning for Chrome users, why you should update it now

description: State Bank of India, HDFC Bank, Canara Bank, ICICI Bank, Axis Bank, and PNB revised their fixed deposit rates. SBI hiked rates by 75 bps for certain tenures, while HDFC raised rates for 18 to just under 21 months. ICICI offers rates up to 7.20% for 15 months to less than 2 years.
title: Banks with highest FD rates: SBI, HDFC, ICICI, PNB...- check list

description: The Department Of School Education Hyderabad released the TS TET 2024 Hall Ticket for the Telangana Teacher Eligibility Test 2024 on tstet2024.aptonline.in. Candidates must review personal details on the admit card.
title: TS TET 2024 hall ticket released

description: The city of Hyderabad experienced heavy rainfall on Thursday, but the Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH) won't be too concerned about the possibility of their Indian Premier League (IPL) match against Gujarat Titans being washed out due to the weather conditions.If the match is called off, then the teams will be awarded one point each, with SRH sealing their place in the IPL 2024 playoffs.
title: IPL: What happens if SRH-GT match gets washed out?

description: Addressing a rally in Bengal's Tamluk, the TMC chief said, "At all India level, some people have misunderstood my statement yesterday. I am very much part of the INDIA alliance. The INDIA alliance was my brainchild. We are together at the national level and will continue to be together," she said.
title: 'Part of INDIA bloc': Mamata's U-turn after 'outside support' remark
Why Sitharaman's reply to broker's question on taxes sparked row

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Thursday took a swipe at Congress leader Rahul Gandhi and SP chief Akhilesh Yadav, saying the 'shehzadas' will leave the country for summer vacation "khatakhat khatakhat' (Hindi colloquial for being quick) the day parliamentary results are announced. He said the 'shehzadas' born in palaces are neither used to hard work nor capable of bringing results.
title: After June 4, 'shehzadas' will run away for vacation 'khatakhat khatakhat', says PM Modi

description: In the ongoing IPL 2024, Sunil Narine, the star opener and spinner for the Kolkata Knight Riders, has been displaying remarkable prowess, crucial to his team's triumphs. Narine's batting proficiency is widely recognized, with his capacity to provide explosive starts. His aggressive style and knack for smashing towering sixes establish him as a dominant force at the beginning of the innings.
title: Sunil Narine surprises fans, dazzles in Bangla language
What Priyanka Gandhi said on Swati Maliwal assault case

description: MIT-educated brothers, Anton and James Peraire-Bueno, charged with $25M Ethereum heist exploiting a system vulnerability. They were taken into custody in Boston and New York, marking a crackdown on illicit activities in the cryptocurrency sector. Legal representatives have yet to respond
title: Gone in 12 seconds: MIT brothers held in $25m crypto heist

description: Taha Shah discusses building chemistry with Sharmin Segal through music and friendship on set, addressing trolls, and working on intense scenes like Eid. He mentions the supportive environment created by Sharmin, missing out on working with Sanjeeda and Richa.
title: Taha Shah reacts to Sharmin Segal getting trolled for 'Heeramandi'

description: Sanju Samson, who has had a good IPL both as a batter and captain for Rajasthan Royals, pipped the likes of KL Rahul and Ishan Kishan to make it into India's T20 World Cup squad as the second wicketkeeper-batter behind Rishabh Pant.
title: 'You are not a newbie': Gambhir to Samson

description: Slovak PM Robert Fico was stable after an assassination attempt by poet Juraj Cintula. The motive is still unclear. Interior Ministry spokesman Neumann confirmed the attack near European elections. Cintula's grievances on reforms and Fico's pro-Russian stance were highlighted. Cintula campaigned against violence. The Son of the gunman was shocked by the incident.
title: Who is Juraj Cintula, poet who fired at Slovak PM

description: Speaking at a rally in Bihar's Sitamarhi, Amit Shah said, "Today Lalu Yadav, for the sake of power politics, to make his son the chief minister, has gone and sat in the lap of the Congress party, which has spent its entire life opposing the backward and extremely backward classes."
title: 'For sake of ...': Amit Shah on why Lalu is with INDIA bloc

description: Blinkit introduces free coriander with vegetable orders following Ankit Sawant's social media feedback on X, causing a mini heart attack. CEO Albinder Dhindsa swiftly implements the free dhaniya feature in response to customer concerns. Customers must purchase vegetables worth at least Rs 500 in Delhi NCR to receive 100 grams of complimentary coriander.
title: How Blinkit plans to solve Indian moms' ‘Dhaniya problem’

description: A study from BHU analyzing the lasting impacts of Bharat Biotech's Covaxin found nearly a third of recipients reported adverse events of special interest (AESI). Among 926 participants, viral upper respiratory tract infections were prevalent. Serious AESI like stroke and Guillain-Barre syndrome were noted in one percent of cases.
title: Over 30% Covaxin recipients faced health issues: Report
'Due to weakness ...': Jaishankar's veiled jab at Nehru over 'losing' PoK

description: Bahadur Singh Parihar, president of a truckers’ union in Jhansi, fined Rs 1,000 by traffic police for not wearing a helmet while driving his Audi car. He visited the RTO office to address the clerical error and was advised to wait until after the Lok Sabha elections.
title: Jhansi man fined for not wearing helmet while driving Audi
How China plans to challenge Boeing, Airbus dominance

description: The Supreme Court on Thursday directed the Union of India to deport 17 foreigners languishing in a Assam detention centre, noting there is no offence registered against them. A bench of Justices Abhay S Oka and Ujjal Bhuyan noted a report submitted by the State Legal Services Authority which stated that there are 17 declared foreigners detained in the detention centre in Assam. "We are of the view that Union of India must take immediate steps for deporting these 17 foreigners as there is no offence registered against them," the bench said.
title: SC directs Centre to deport 17 foreigners languishing in Assam detention centre

description: Indians are exploring key markets with a surge in visits to Japan, Vietnam, and the US. Top summer holiday destinations include Amsterdam, Singapore, and London. The Mastercard report shows a growth in Indian travel due to a growing middle class and expanded route capacity.
title: Indians travelling like never before; top int'l destinations this summer

description: Hitting out at the INDIA alliance for not announcing its PM candidate, home minister Amit Shah on Thursday said "the country needs a strong PM, not one on yearly-basis". The home minister was addressing an election rally in Bihar's Madhubani. The home minister also hit out at the alliance leaders for its recent remarks on Pakistan.
title: After Ram temple, we will now build Sita temple: Amit Shah
Crossword puzzle hints at unsolved 1976 kidnapping in US
Warren Buffett's $6.7bn-bet on insurance giant

description: Michael Hussey hopes Mahendra Singh Dhoni continues batting well for Chennai Super Kings after resigning as captain for the 2024 season, handing over to Ruturaj Gaikwad. Dhoni, who led the team to multiple IPL titles, is managing workload post-knee surgery. He surprised by not attending captains' meeting, indicating Gaikwad as the new captain.
title: 'I hope he...': Michael Hussey on MS Dhoni's retirement call
Man missing for 27 yrs found alive in neighbor's cellar in Algeria

description: Talking about Mamata Banerjee's "outside support" to the INDIA alliance, Congress's Adhir Ranjan Chowdhary said, "I don't trust her (Mamata). She left the alliance and ran away. She can also go towards the BJP if the results are favourable to them ... Everyone has seen that she was the one who broke the alliance."
title: 'Don't trust Mamata': Adhir on 'outside support' remark

description: At least 90 individuals hospitalized after consuming food at a temple feast in Nanded district, Maharashtra due to suspected food poisoning. The incident took place in Naigaon with devotees given 'ambil' and 'khir'. All individuals are in stable condition.
title: 90 hospitalized after consuming food at temple feast in Maha

description: Rakhi Sawant hospitalized for health issues like fibrosis and heart problems. Falguni disputes Adil's claims about court hearing, mentions upcoming surgery. Adil accused of seeking publicity, was in jail during Rakhi's tests. Legal steps to be taken following Supreme Court directions.
title: Rakhi Sawant's lawyer quashes ex-husband Adil Khan claims

description: Banks adjust MCLR monthly based on factors like repo rate. Latest MCLR rates from top 7 banks in May 2024 highlighted. Banks cannot lend below MCLR except in specific cases. Rates effective from specific dates. Consumer loans linked to 1-year MCLR. Yes Bank and Canara Bank rates effective from specific dates. IDBI Bank and SBI rates also provided.
title: Loan interest rates: SBI, HDFC Bank, BoB, PNB in May 2024

description: Telangana AAR clarifies CIAV's services to foreign universities as non-GST exports if payments are in foreign exchange. Independent contractor status and foreign universities' locations outside India support the exempt classification.
title: GST AAR: Acting as a marketing/ recruiting to int univ can qualify as exports

description: The Mumbai Indians camp shares a funny video of Ishan Kishan challenging the giant David. Ishan charges at David's legs in a playful manner. MI, the five-time champions, have one league match left against Lucknow Super Giants in IPL 2024.
title: Watch: Ishan Kishan tests wrestling skills against Tim David

description: The Supreme Court on Thursday held that the Enforcement Directorate cannot arrest an accused person after the special court has taken cognizance of the complaint. A bench of justices Abhay S Oka and Ujjal Bhuyan also made it clear that if ED requires custody, then the probe agency can move the application before the concerned court and thereafter, the court can only grant custody once satisfied with the reasons that custodial interrogation is required.
title: ED can't arrest after special court takes cognizance of PMLA complaint: SC

description: Apple's 'crush' ad for iPad Pro faced backlash, leading to an apology. Samsung's Galaxy Tab S9 ad promotes creativity amidst Apple's hydraulic press aftermath. Apple's VP of marketing communications, Tor Myhren, apologized for missing the mark with the video.
title: Samsung makes fun of Apple; says, 'would never crush creativity'
Swati Maliwal assault case: NCW summons Kejriwal's former PS

description: A 32-year-old woman from Delhi lost Rs 23.5 lakh to a ‘fake’ investment website in a cyber fraud incident. The victim's case unfolded a detailed investigation by Deputy Commissioner of Police Joy Tirkey, uncovering the recovery of funds from multiple bank accounts and the modus operandi of the accused.
title: Delhi woman loses over Rs 23 lakh in share market fraud

description: Two people died and three others were injured in Noida after a speeding BMW X4 rammed into an e-rickshaw. The deceased were identified as Mohammad Mustafa and Rashmi, while the injured included Rajendra, Pawan, and Suraj, who are undergoing treatment. Two individuals, Tushar and Adi, were arrested, and one, Aman Sisodia, fled the scene.
title: Two killed, three injured as BMW rams e-rickshaw in Noida
'Did not make any exception': SC refuses to consider ED objection to Kejriwal's campaign speech

description: Spinny reports growth in used car sales for Jan-April CY2024, with a surge in first-time buyers opting for popular brands and models. Compact SUVs, hatchbacks, and luxury cars show demand, with specific preferences in colors. Top cities for sales highlighted, along with transmission trends. Follow TOI Auto for updates.
title: Bengaluru, Hyderabad lead used car sales in India

description: Delhi CM Kejriwal silent on Swati Maliwal assault, passing mic to party colleague Singh at press conference. AAP MP questions PM Modi's silence on various issues. Maliwal allegedly assaulted by Kejriwal's assistant. BJP protests over safety issue.
title: Kejriwal refrains from commenting on Swati Maliwal assault case

description: Indian telecom companies and VoICE group push for govt action against Chinese imports, advocating self-reliance in the sector with stricter controls on traders and measures to blacklist shell companies.
title: TCS, HFCL & Tejas make 'Chinese complaint' to govt against Cisco & others

description: Misbah-ul-Haq has emphasized the importance of Babar Azam's performance in T20 cricket, highlighting the need for adaptability and maintaining an optimal strike rate. With the T20 World Cup in June, Misbah praised Babar's recent 75-run innings against Ireland, highlighting his explosive knocks and ability to adjust his batting approach according to the team's requirements.
title: 'Important for Babar Azam to not bat at 130-140 strike rate'
'Would have made Hirak Rani': Amit Shah takes dig at Mamata
More important issues than Swati Maliwal: Akhilesh Yadav

description: Silver is expected to outperform gold with a 15-20% potential increase. Expectations of gains in industrial metals globally and China's recovery could boost silver to Rs 100,000 per kilogram.
title: Silver set to outperform gold? Metal likely to cross Rs 1L mark

description: Author Amitav Ghosh warned about Mumbai's billboards becoming dangerous during cyclones in his book 'The Great Derangement', emphasizing climate change impact on informal settlements with metal roofs and billboards, posing a threat to citizens.
title: Amitav Ghosh predicted 8 years ago about Mumbai hoardings

description: Soon after Chhetri's announced that the World Cup qualification game against Kuwait on June 6 will be his last in the India jersey, timelines across social media platforms were flooded with #HappyRetirementLegend messages, led by none other that Chhetri's friend and cricket legend Virat Kohli, who wrote "My brother. Proud."
title: 'My brother, proud': Virat Kohli messages retiring Sunil Chhetri
Watch: Hezbollah's 60 missile blitz burns Israel

description: Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra has expressed concern over Rajasthan Royals' recent losses in the Indian Premier League, despite their playoff qualification based on favorable results from other matches. Chopra's comments came after the Royals' fourth consecutive defeat against Punjab Kings in Guwahati, despite already securing a spot in the top four.
title: 'What has happened, RR guys?': Ex-cricketer on the losing streak

description: Apple iPhone 15 and Samsung Galaxy S24 dominated the super-premium segment in the Indian smartphone market in Q1 2024, as per IDC report. Apple had 69% and Samsung 31% market share. Top models: Apple iPhone 14, 14 Plus, Samsung Galaxy S24, S24+, and more. The segment grew 44% with 34M shipments, increasing market share from 7% to 9%.
title: iPhone 15 to S24: 'Highest selling super-premium phones in India'

description: Panic on Delhi-Vadodara Air India Flight at IGI Airport as crew member finds 'bomb' note in washroom, triggering search but no suspicious item found; Passengers disembarked for security check before departing on another aircraft for their destination.
title: Fake 'bomb' note sparks panic onboard Delhi-Vadodara flight

description: ICICI Bank issues cautionary notice about fraudulent IVR calls used by fraudsters to deceive and obtain sensitive information from customers. Safety tips include verifying caller legitimacy and avoiding sharing sensitive information over the phone.
title: ICICI Bank's important warning on 'customer service frauds'

description: Shekhar Suman plans to revive 'Movers & Shakers' and is keen to host an exclusive chat with PM Narendra Modi, discussing Modi's journey, challenges, and societal contributions. Currently, the actor is riding high on the success of his OTT series 'Heeramandi' which was directed by Sanjay Leela Bhansali.
title: Shekhar Suman wants to interview PM Modi on his TV show

description: Infosys' NR Narayana Murthy and S 'Kris' Gopalakrishnan have urged upcoming new government to focus on fostering entrepreneurship which in turn will lead to job creation, wealth generation and more tax revenue.
title: Narayana Murthy wants new government to focus on ...
Chidambaram slams PM Modi's '15% budget to Muslims' charge

description: Irfan Pathan has expressed concerns over Yashasvi Jaiswal's form in the Indian Premier League, suggesting that his lean run could prompt the Indian team to reconsider their opening combination for the T20 World Cup. Jaiswal's recent struggles, including a fourth consecutive defeat against Rajasthan Royals, have highlighted his potential influence on India's decision.
title: 'Virat, Rohit as openers': Irfan raises concerns over Jaiswal's form
If BJP comes to power, Yogi will be replaced as UP CM: Kejriwal

description: Namita Thapar shines at Cannes, discussing entrepreneurship and fertility awareness. Aman Gupta and Pia Dagger share amusing looks. She was a standout investor on 'Shark Tank India', sparking viral internet memes.
title: Shark Tank India's Namita Thapar debuts in Cannes 2024

description: India's football icon Sunil Chhetri on Thursday announced his decision to retire from international football after the country's FIFA World Cup qualification match against Kuwait on June 6. The national team captain announced his decision via a video he posted on his social media accounts.
title: Football icon Sunil Chhetri announces retirement

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, rose in early trade on Thursday. While BSE Sensex was up over 390 points, Nifty50 was above 22,300.
title: Sensex up almost 400 points; Nifty50 above 22,300

description: Slovak PM Robert Fico is in a critical but stable condition after being shot multiple times in an incident described by officials as a "political assault." The 59-year-old leader underwent lengthy surgery as medical teams fought to save his life. The attack has sparked international condemnation. Reflecting on the surgery, Deputy PM Tomas Taraba optimistically told the BBC, "I guess in the end he will survive. He's not in a life-threatening situation at this moment."
title: 'A wake-up call to West': Europe on edge after attempt on Slovak PM's life
Who Is Robert Fico? All you need to know about Slovak PM

description: Magician David Copperfield has been accused of sexual misconduct by more than a dozen women in episodes said to have taken place over several decades, a report said Wednesday. The Guardian said its investigation had uncovered allegations from 16 women that the celebrated US illusionist had behaved inappropriately towards them, including some who said they were under 18 at the time. Three of the women claim Copperfield drugged them before sex.
title: 'Multiple women accuse David Copperfield of sex misconduct'

description: Heat wave poses health risks, IMD forecasts using meteorological parameters. It can cause dehydration, illnesses in vulnerable populations. Ministry of Earth Sciences (MoES) plays a role in predictions.
title: What is heatwave? How extreme temperatures affect human body

description: Russian President Vladimir Putin arrived in China on Thursday to meet with counterpart Xi Jinping as he seeks greater support from Beijing for his war effort in Ukraine and his isolated economy. Xi, who returned last week from a three-nation tour of Europe, has rebuffed Western criticism of his country's ties with Moscow, enjoying cheap Russian energy imports and access to vast natural resources, including steady gas shipments via the Power of Siberia pipeline.
title: Who is the 'big brother' between 2 'presidents for life': Xi or Putin?

description: Virat Kohli has influenced the sporting world like none other over the past decade, which also played a role in cricket being included in the Olympic programme for the Los Angeles 2028 edition of the Games. And as the India batting icon's hunger for runs refuses to cease, it's quite natural for fans and experts to ask what keeps him going.
title: Virat Kohli: 'Once I'm done, you won't see me for a while'

description: Pakistani lawmaker Syed Mustafa Kamal drew a comparison between India's achievements and the precarious situation in Karachi, by mentioning India's moon landing mission. The Muttahida Quami Movement Pakistan (MQM-P) leader said that while India is landing on the moon, Karachi is making news of children being killed by falling in open gutters. He further highlighted the lack of fresh water in Karachi. The MQM-P leader also said citing a report that there are 70 lakh children in Karachi and over 2.6 crore children in Pakistan, who are not able to go to schools.
title: 'India landed on moon, while we ... ': Pakistani lawmaker
State of emergency in France amid unrest in New Caledonia

description: Kolkata Knight Riders have secured the top position in the Indian Premier League points table for the first time in the franchise's history. The team's impressive record of nine wins and three losses in 13 matches has led them to 19 points, while Rajasthan Royals' fourth consecutive defeat further hindered their chances of securing a top-two finish.
title: KKR secure top spot on points table for first time in IPL history

description: Eight people lost their lives and one person was injured in a fatal accident on the Indore-Ahmedabad Highway near Betma in Madhya Pradesh's Indore district. The victims were on their way to Guna when their SUV collided with an unidentified vehicle on the four-lane highway. The bodies have been sent for post-mortem examination.
title: 8 killed after two vehicles collide on Indore-Ahd highway

description: Nassau County Ground inaugurated by Usain Bolt for T20 World Cup matches in the USA. The stadium, with a capacity of 34,000, will host the India-Pakistan game. ICC ensured international standards. United States Cricket focuses on success in the new market. Chris Tetley and Damian Hough oversee pitch preparations in Florida. The galleries for the venue are makeshift. The temporary structure will be brought in from the Formula One track of Las Vegas and returned after the tournament is over.
title: 'Indo-Pak T20 WC game venue in NY will match Wankhede in size'

description: A 32-year-old woman in Delhi was scammed through a Telegram channel, part of a larger trend of investment fraud. Scammers lure victims with high returns, fake stock tips, and vanish after large deposits. The scams involve fake websites, spoofed websites, marketing tools, and resources from the dark web.
title: Guru's stock tips: How Telegram channels turned dreams into nightmares for 200 investors

description: Kolkata Police warn of fraudsters using Covid vaccine concerns to extract Aadhaar numbers and bank details via IVRS calls, freezing phones to access personal and financial information. Doctors reassure minimal risk from vaccines, citing low incidence of Covishield-related TTS cases among 85 crore people who received two doses.
title: Covishield scare is scamsters' latest weapon to get personal info

description: Somy Ali appeals to Bishnoi community to forgive Salman Khan for poaching incidents during 'Ham Saath Saath Hain' filming. Bishnoi Tiger Force opposes forgiveness, calls for legal action to continue. Cases in courts from high court to Supreme Court against Khan.
title: Bishnois split as Somy Ali asks them to pardon Salman Khan

description: Bhavesh Bhinde, head of Ego Media Pvt Ltd, earned Rs 25 crore annually from the Ghatkopar hoarding that crashed in 2022. Former BJP MP Kirit Somaiya alleged the hoarding was the largest among four, paying GRP an annual rent of Rs 24 lakh for the welfare fund.
title: 'Ex-MP claims Bhavesh Bhinde got Rs 25cr from 4 hoardings'

description: Punjab Kings defeated Rajasthan Royals, thanks to skipper Sam Curran's exceptional all-round performance. The win provided Punjab with a consolation victory but impacted Rajasthan's hopes of a top-two finish in the league stage. Rajasthan and Kolkata are the only teams to secure a play-off berth. Curran's performance emphasized Punjab's determination to finish the season positively.
title: IPL playoff scenarios: Five teams in hunt for the last two spots

description: Google I/O, led by CEO Sundar Pichai, highlighted advancements in Gemini AI models, Trillium TPUs, and liquid cooling systems, catering to 2 billion users.
title: 7 key numbers CEO Pichai mentioned on stage during Google keynote

description: Former cricketers have favoured Chennai Super Kings over Royal Challengers Bengaluru in the Indian Premier League due to MS Dhoni's presence and the team's record in pressure situations. Mohammad Kaif highlighted Dhoni's role in India's 2011 World Cup triumph and CSK's history of success in knockout games, highlighting CSK's position as frontrunners against RCB.
title: 'Dhoni galtiyan kam karte hai, isliye CSK champion team hai'

description: China's measured response to US tariffs reflects a restrained approach in trade tensions. Notably, the Biden administration informed Chinese officials in advance and targeted industries dominated by Chinese companies. This dynamic contrasts with past escalations, showcasing Beijing's confidence in protecting its interests.
title: 'What doesn't kill you makes you stronger,' China trolls new US tariffs
‘Fire & ice’: A clash of contrasts in UP's Amethi as poll battle hots up
